  <!-- ═══ RISKS ═══ -->
  <h2>Key Risks to the Valuation</h2>
  <p>Our intrinsic value calculation assumes business as usual. Here are the primary risks that could challenge this assumption.</p>

  <h3>Upside risks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>GenAI explosion:</strong> If enterprise adoption of Generative AI accelerates sharply, Accenture's consulting and implementation revenues could significantly beat our 8% growth assumption.</li>
    <li><strong>Aggressive M&A:</strong> Accenture uses its strong cash flows to continually acquire smaller, high-growth niche tech consultancies, which can further compound growth.</li>
    <li><strong>Margin expansion:</strong> Further structural shifts toward higher-value services could push margins higher, generating more FCF per dollar of revenue.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Downside risks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Corporate IT budget cuts:</strong> As a service provider, ACN is vulnerable to macroeconomic downturns. If large corporations freeze their IT or consulting budgets, growth will stall.</li>
    <li><strong>Wage inflation:</strong> As a talent-driven business, rising wages for highly skilled consultants and engineers can squeeze operating margins.</li>
    <li><strong>In-sourcing trends:</strong> If clients decide to build tech capabilities internally rather than outsourcing, Accenture's long-term growth ceiling could drop.</li>
  </ul>

